Botswana Increases Fuel Prices by 6.9% on Higher International Oil Costs

-- B y   J e r r y   B u n g u
-- 
2011-08-19T04:47:41Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-19/botswana-increases-fuel-prices-by-6-9-on-higher-international-oil-costs.html
Botswana  raised fuel prices by 6.9
percent because of higher international  oil prices .  Gasoline will increase by 50 thebe to 7.70 pula ($1.14) per
liter, while diesel will rise by the same margin to 7.75 pula
and kerosene to 5.90 pula, the Minerals, Energy and Water
Resources Ministry said in an e-mailed statement yesterday from
Gaborone, the capital.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jerry Bungu in Gaborone at 
 jbungu@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Paul Richardson  at 
 pmrichardson@bloomberg.net  